rComments: Prof. Davis' philosophy is to throw all the material he can at the students and grin as he watches it bounce back. Lectures are very fast-paced, oftentimes too fast-paced to follow and Prof. Davis doesn't seem to care about the class. He thinks it's funny to give impossible-to-finish tests. I think he should have more respect for his students.

clear. concise, fair.  big bell curve, which lets you not answer a few midterm questions and still get an A.  Proofs always come up, but you can use your free questions to avoid the hard ones.
